        "timestamp": "2021-02-19 03:02:59.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n(2 comments)\n\nHum ... looking at this change in detail, I'm challenging it as REST, by convention, usually manages items from collections.\n\nFor example, endpoint to retrieve a unique item by its id is `/items/{id}`\n\nAlso endpoint to filter from a list of items would be `/items?param={value}`\n\nAnd it seems to me that this what we are doing here, we are filtering from the list of nodes using xpath query parameter. Then, even if some filter can return one element, I would still stay aligned with the REST convention and I would keep the nodes plural for the get.\n\nFor an additional reading about REST API design: https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/azure/architecture/best-practices/api-design\n\nWhat do you think ?",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
